sentence: Paul Christopher, J. D. Salinger ' s Holden Caulfield, and J. P. Donleavy ' s Sebastion Dangerfield in The Ginger Man (1955) are among the post-World War II literary heroes who have stymied Hollywood efforts to depict them.see J.P. Donnelley, 91, Author Who Stirred Controversy With ' Ginger Man, ' Dies, The New York Times, September 14, 2017.
